A poster for iQiyi's The Thunder Photo: Courtesy of iQiyiStreaming drama The Thunder, based on the real crime case of China's biggest drug trafficking ring, is set to hit Chinese streaming site iQiyi on May 7, the platform announced on Sunday. The 48-episode drama starring young heartthrob Huang Jingyu and veteran actors Wu Gang, Wang Jinsong and Simon Yam, tells the story about Li Fei, a young anti-drug police officer, as he tackles a drug-trafficking ring based in a small village in South China. Boshe village in South China's Guangdong Province was once called the country's "top drug-production village" as it supplied over one-third of the nation's crystal meth, according to a Xinhua News Agency report in 2018. More than 3,000 police officers raided the village in the early morning of December 29, 2013, seizing roughly three tons of crystal meth and capturing more than 180 suspects in one of the biggest cases in history. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Delegation of HUST attends alumni gala in Los AngelesChinese driving Vegas growthHaving fun